parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wiring harness can cause the engine to stall, misfire, and overheat, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents. Additionally, the faulty wiring harness can lead to electrical fires, putting the occupants and vehicle at risk.
symptoms: and overheating; sudden loss of power and stalling while driving; burning smell; faulty indicators; cracked or disintegrated wiring harness insulation; exposed wires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft flex disk can cause the engine to lock up, resulting in sudden loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents and potentially deploy airbags.
Unintended airbag deployment can cause distractions, injuries, or accidents, and may also lead to unnecessary repair costs.
symptoms: airbag deploys in the absence of a crash
airbag warning lights illuminate on the dashboard.
